193
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:35,040
Yo, admit it, you're messing with me, aren't you?

194
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:36,000
Nope.

195
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:37,800
What's it gonna be, truth or dare?

196
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:38,720
Truth.

197
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:41,000
Alright, let me spin to see who's asking you.

198
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:41,520
Umm.

199
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:44,680
As long as it's not you.

200
00:12:44,880 --> 00:12:45,800
(Ing.)

201
00:12:49,160 --> 00:12:53,480
If you go easy on him or help him, you have to finish your drink.

202
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:54,560
I know.

203
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:56,240
Ask.

204
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:57,720
Then let me ask you.

205
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:58,240
Um.

206
00:12:58,360 --> 00:13:01,000
The most embarrassing thing that you haven't told anyone yet.

207
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:04,880
If it's embarrassing, should I really tell it?

208
00:13:05,280 --> 00:13:07,000
Well, it's a question.

209
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:09,960
Drink up, if you don't tell.

210
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:12,120
Fine, I'll tell.

211
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:13,280
It must be like this.

212
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:14,360
It must be like this!

213
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:16,480
So, about two months ago,

214
00:13:16,480 --> 00:13:18,400
I went out to eat, right?

215
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:20,560
And that day, it was raining really hard.

216
00:13:20,560 --> 00:13:22,440
So, I was going up the pedestrian bridge,

217
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:24,280
and while I was going up, I tripped on the stairs.

218
00:13:24,760 --> 00:13:26,440
And my flip-flop drifted off.

219
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:28,800
Don't tell me...

220
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:32,640
Yeah, it flew right into a crowd of people waiting for the bus.

221
00:13:34,040 --> 00:13:37,000
When I went to pick it up, I was both hurt and embarrassed.

222
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:39,080
When I went down, I fell in this position.

223
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,160
Whoa, whoa, stop.

224
00:13:40,160 --> 00:13:41,280
Clam down.

225
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:43,520
Oh man, that almost hit my face.

226
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:46,360
You've been clumsy since you were a kid, huh?

227
00:13:50,080 --> 00:13:51,160
Is it my turn?

228
00:13:51,160 --> 00:13:51,840
Yeah.

229
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:53,560
I hope it lands on you, Yo.

230
00:13:53,560 --> 00:13:55,160
Bring it on, I'm not afraid.

231
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,480
(Yo)

232
00:13:59,480 --> 00:14:01,400
